Description: Rim and handle sherd (mended from three fragments) of grey ware pottery trefoil oinochoe with handle root; dark grey fabric core with lighter brown halo; mica inclusions; thick, very dark grey (almost black) slip on exterior; thin walled; thickened offset rim and strap handle.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.260, no.4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.165)
